        <Parent_String>textile materials by process or technique [300231603], textile materials [300231565], fiber by product [300014062], fiber and fiber by product [300014023], materials by physical form [300247256], materials by form [300014611], materials (substances) [300010358], Materials (hierarchy name) [300010357], Materials Facet [300264091]</Parent_String>
        <Hier_Rel_Type>Genus/Species-BTG</Hier_Rel_Type>
      </Preferred_Parent>
    </Parent_Relationships>
    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Stiff, durable textile characterized by corded effects in either the warp or weft, originally made in white cotton, later also in rayon or silk, and printed or in colors; used for dresses, blouses, trousers, sports clothing, purses, and neckwear.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000099620/Legacy AAT data</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Textil rígido, durable, caracterizado por efectos de cuerda en la trama o en la urdimbre. Originalmente de algodón blanco; posteriormente también en rayón o seda y estampado o en colores. Utilizado para vestidos, blusas, pantalones, ropa deportiva, bolsos y echarpes.
</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Stijve, duurzame textiel die wordt gekenmerkt door geribbelde effecten in ofwel de schering of de inslag. Oorspronkelijk alleen gemaakt van witte katoen, later ook van kunstvezel of zijde, bedrukt of in kleur; wordt gebruikt voor jurken, blouses, broeken, sportkleding, handtassen en dassen.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
